                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15190.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State ad interim</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister to Mexico</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-11T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 11, 1915—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>770. Your 623, June 10, 11 a.m. Discreetly impress upon authorities in control
                    that any harsh measures of reprisal would create a most unfavorable impression
                    abroad, and might, by adding to the acuteness of the political situation, retard
                    the efforts to extend measures of relief to the destitute.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
